# Allowlist approach: exclude everything from the docker build context, then
# re-include only what the Dockerfile actually needs. Keeps the context tiny
# (the Dockerfile only COPYs entrypoint.sh) and prevents unrelated files —
# .git/, tests/, docs/, README, host-specific cruft — from being shipped to
# the docker daemon on every build.

*

!Dockerfile
!entrypoint.sh
